label.value: Stage II Extrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA: (T3, N0, M0); IIB: (T1, N1, M0); (T2, N1, M0); (T3, N1, M0).  T3: Tumor invades the liver, gallbladder, pancreas, and/or unilateral branches or the portal vein (right or left) or hepatic artery (right or left).  N1: Regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.)

Stage III Extrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer

value.value: Stage III includes: T4, Any N, M0.  T4: Tumor invades any of the following main portal vein or its branches bilaterally, common hepatic artery, or other adjacent structures, such as the colon, stomach, duodenum, or abdominal wall.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.)
